Company Overview
EMRISE Corporation designs, manufactures, and markets electronic devices, sub-systems, and equipment for aerospace, defense, industrial, and communications markets primarily in North America, Europe, North Africa, and Asia. The company operates through two segments, Electronic Devices and Communications Equipment. The Electronic Devices segment produces power systems, including high and low voltage, high specification, and custom and standard power conversion products for hostile environments; radio frequency and microwave devices, such as frequency control products, custom integrated assemblies, and sub-systems that are used in various applications, including communications, air traffic con...
EMRISE Corporation designs, manufactures, and markets electronic devices, sub-systems, and equipment for aerospace, defense, industrial, and communications markets primarily in North America, Europe, North Africa, and Asia. The company operates through two segments, Electronic Devices and Communications Equipment. The Electronic Devices segment produces power systems, including high and low voltage, high specification, and custom and standard power conversion products for hostile environments; radio frequency and microwave devices, such as frequency control products, custom integrated assemblies, and sub-systems that are used in various applications, including communications, air traffic control, navigation and location equipment, radar and signal jamming devices, weather radar, and others; and sub-system assemblies. This segment offers commercial and military electronic devices primarily to original equipment manufacturers, including manufacturers of aerospace and defense systems, and industrial equipment. The Communications Equipment segment provides network access products comprising a range of LAN/WAN interconnection equipment and systems over copper, fiber, or wireless networks that are used in various markets, such as military, utilities and other private networks, government administration, and point of sale and public communications service providers. This segment also offers timing and synchronization products for the outer edges of service provider networks for telephone companies, cable carriers, government administration, utility companies, and other defense and homeland security related applications. The company sells its products through direct sales and independent representatives, in-house sales force, and third-party distributors. EMRISE Corporation was founded in 1973 and is based in Durham, North Carolina.
